description: Get your zoodle on with this poached egg recipe. The zucchini noodles are baked with garlic and tomatoes, then topped with basil, poached eggs and parmesan.
keywords: Breakfast,Seafood free,Gluten free,Tree nut free,Weeknight dinner,Sesame free,Budget,Summer,Zucchini,High fibre,Autumn,Apr 2021,Pescatarian,Low salt,Quick & easy breakfast,Egg,Low sugar,Halal,High protein,Vegetarian,Soy free,Wheat free,Tomato,Peanut free
name: Poached Eggs With Roasted Tomato & Zoodles Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and place tomatoes on 1 tray. Drizzle with half the oil. Season and bake for 10 minutes or until starting to soften.

Meanwhile, combine zucchini spaghetti, garlic and remaining oil in a large bowl. Season with pepper and toss to combine. Add zucchini mixture to remaining tray and bake for the last 7 minutes of tomato cooking time or until warmed through.

Meanwhile, half-fill a large, shallow frying pan with water and bring to the boil. Break 1 egg in a cup, then slide into pan. Repeat with remaining eggs. Cook for 3 minutes or until whites are set and yolks are cooked to your liking. Remove with a slotted spoon to a paper towel-lined plate.
Divide zucchini mixture and tomatoes among plates. Top with egg, parmesan and basil. Serve seasoned with pepper.
